<dl id="s15049m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us15" href="#s15049m">Circe: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s15all.htm#s15049m">sector 49(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> body, soul &amp; spirit</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo;Earth&rsquo; &hellip; So gradually the earth lover realises the golden world is all about him in imperishable beauty, and he may pass from the vision to the profounder beauty of being, and know an eternal love is within and around him, pressing upon him and sustaining with infinite tenderness <mark>his body, his soul and his spirit</mark>. <small> A. E. (George Russell). <a name="AECV1" href="/udra/udex.htm#AECV1"><cite title="source">The Candle of Vision</cite></a> (1918), 172</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
